French Style Pork Stew
  --America's Test Kitchen

6 parsley sprigs + 1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley
3 large sprigs fresh thyme
5 garlic cloves, unpeeled
2 bay leaves
1 tbsp black peppercorns
2 whole cloves
5 c water
4 c chicken broth
3 lbs bonelss pork butt roast, trimmed and cut into 1-1 1/2" pieces
1 meaty smoked ham shank or 2-3 smoked ham hocks (1 1/4 lb)
2 onions, halved through root end, root end left intact
4 carrots, peeled, narrow end cut crosswise into 1/2" pieces, wide end halved lengthwise and cut into 1/2" pieces
1 lb yukon gold potatoes, unpeeled, cut into 3/4" pieces
12 oz kielbasa sausage, halved lengthwise, and then cut into 1/2" thick slices
1/2 head savoy cabbage, shredded (8 c)

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 325F. Cut 10" square of triple thickness cheesecloth. Place parsley sprigs (fold or break to fit), thyme sprigs, garlic, bay leaves, peppercorns, and cloves in center of cheesecloth and tie into bundle with kitchen twine. Bring water, broth, pok, ham, onion, and hreb bundle to simmer in large dutch oven over medium high heat, skimming off scum that rises to surface. Cover pot and place in oven. Cook until pork chunks are tender and skewer inserted into meat meets little resistance, 75-890 min. Using slotted spoon, discard onion and herb bundle. Transfer ham to plate. Add carrots and potatoes  to pot and stir to combine. Cover and return to oven. Cook until vegetables are almost tender, 20-25 min. When ham is cool enough to handle, using 2 forks, remove meat and shred into bite size pieces; discard skin and bones. Add shredded ham, kielbasa, and cabbage to pot. Stir to combine, cover, and return to oven. Cook until kielbasa is heated through and cabbage is wilted and tender, 15-20 min. Season with salt and pepper to taste, then stir in chopped parsley. 
